procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and pregnancy tests.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum measurement.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate and intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc).

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

code.decode: Office or other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of an established patient

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring and collection of information on adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Clinical Safety Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Lab Tests
procedures.description: Laboratory assessments including serum chemistry, hematology, and coagulation.

procedures.name: Infectious Disease Screening
procedures.label: HIV, Hepatitis Screen
procedures.description: Screening for HIV, hepatitis B and C.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: Cannulation
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples of all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements, including recording weight and time of each bowel movement.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Device
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Device used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
